<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853.51/304</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1925</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received December 17.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1272</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose to the
                            Department herewith a copy of the <hi rend="italic">Diario do
                                Governo</hi> No. 258 dated November 28, 1925, which appeared only at
                            noon today, containing the text of the decree, No. 11, 289,<note n="11" xml:id="d559fn11">Not printed.</note> authorizing the Minister of
                            Finance to carry out the immediate liquidation of the balance of the
                            debt arising from the bonds of the 4½% Tobacco Loan of 1891 and 1896, in
                            the form that may be most compatible with the interests of the State.
                            …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fred Morris
                            Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>